******
[2] São Paulo State
Date: Fri 2 Feb 2018, 5:17 PM BRST
Source: CBN, ACidadeON report [in Portuguese, trans. Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ, edited]
http://www.cbnribeirao.com.br/noticias/NOT,2,2,1304768,advogada+de+52+anos+internada+ha+um+mes+esta+com+botulismo.aspx


The Health Department of Ribeirão Preto [São Paulo state] confirmed the [diagnosis of botulism in the case of a 52-year-old lawyer hospitalized a month ago at the Hospital São Lucas] and reported that there are 2 more suspected cases under investigation. According to the documentation, these 2 patients also present neurological alterations that could be caused by botulism.

According to [her daughter], the lawyer was hospitalized on [2 Jan 2018] with dizziness, nausea, weakness, photophobia, and difficulty swallowing. "Initially we thought she had had a stroke, but at the hospital, after the tests, the doctor ruled it out and suspected botulism," says the daughter. The lawyer was hospitalized at about 5:30 pm. At 11 pm on the same day she was transferred to the ICU (intensive care unit), where she had a respiratory arrest. The next day, even before the results of the tests were announced, the patient had already received antibotulin serum.

However, the appearance of neurological changes on day 4 made the medical team also suspect the patient was suffering from Guillain-Barré syndrome, but the disease was later ruled out.

The lawyer, who was hospitalized in the ICU for 20 days, suffered paralysis of the limbs. She is already in a room, where she is gradually regaining her movements, but her discharge is not being considered. "She is still breathing with assisted ventilation, but she has reacted well. She can open her eyes and she is conscious," says the daughter, who adds that the lawyer can already move her hands and legs, change her body position and, although she does not yet speak due to a tracheostomy, she communicates with her children through writing. "We are very optimistic that the risk phase of the disease has passed and now we expect all movement to return."

The daughter praised the rapid medical intervention and accurate diagnosis of the team of Hospital São Lucas. "As doctors suspected from the outset that it could be botulism and have already administered the serum, the chance of full recovery is 100 percent. "

ACidadeON news tried to contact neurologist Francisco Coletto, head of the team responsible for the lawyer's case, but could not contact him. A message was left with his secretary at his private practice, but at the time of publication of this report, there had been no response.

Health surveillance
-------------------
The lawyer's daughter said that the Sanitary Surveillance took milk and a soy cheese from the patient's home to try to determine the origin of the bacteria that caused the disease. According to the health department, the material was sent to Adolfo Lutz for analysis and the results are awaited.

[Byline: Rita Magalhães]

